		<!--ANSWERS BEGINS HERE-->		
<!-- a href=mailto:myriad@microtec.net -->
This Payola is the real dope; it's already allowed me to experience
greater paranoia than ever before! Absolutely fantastic! All
Diplomacy games should be played like this...
<P>
The fact that the bids are secret allow you to make bald faced lies
with minimal chance of discovery. You could get away with telling
your enemy you're his friend even as your forces decimate his
homeland! I'd think often your closest ally is also your worst
enemy. And the ability to manipulate the other nations'
relationships by taking control of their armies and creating
stress... you could arrange wars between your neighbours to free up
your fronts (and I'm sure this is a common strategy). Having a lot
of fun...

Rave, rave, rave, rave...
		<!--ANSWERS ENDS HERE-->
	</td>
