<!-- a href=mailto:maurich@xilinx.com -->
</font></H4>
WOW!!!!  Payola is awesome.
<P>
In this 1898 Payola game, I am taking a different strategy than standard.
So far, while
there are still neutral supply centers around, I am playing with people in
the Spring so they cannot achieve their goals that Fall of taking their
home supply centers.  As a consequence, as Italy I am ready for an attack
on France this next year that would never be possible in standard
Diplomacy.  It would even be tough in standard 1898.  Longer term, I am
playing around with Britain so he won't be in a position to defend
himself against me when it is his turn.
<P>
Interesting about no-press Payola....  Before I even did anything,
Austria had transferred 1 AgP to me.  After briefly wondering about
this, I recognized it as an offer for an alliance.  To signal acceptance,
all I needed to do was give it back!
	</td>
	</tr>
