	<table border=0 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	<tr valign=top>
	<td class="bodycopy">
A special character of Payola is the difficulty in 
conducting combined operations requiring several units. Combined 
operations are still possible, but they require superior finances and 
the readiness to put them at stake (besides that, you'll want to 
have a pretty good idea of the counter-bidding threshold). That's 
why, for instance, the Lepanto opening is unusual in Payola. 
Early on, Italy simply lacks funds to make it work.
<p>
Payola is a strategic game in which tactical aspects play a 
subordinate role.

	</td>
	</tr>
